title: Omar Benrabah Stadium
text:
Omar Benrabah Stadium is a multi-use <a href="stadium">stadium</a> located in the <a href="Dar%20El%20Be%C3%AFda">Dar El Beïda</a> district of <a href="Algiers">Algiers</a>, <a href="Algeria">Algeria</a>. It is currently used mostly for <a href="Association%20football">football</a> matches. It is frequently used by the <a href="Algeria%20A%27%20national%20football%20team">Algeria A' national football team</a> and the <a href="Algeria%20Olympic%20football%20team">Algerian Under-23 National Team</a>. also is the home ground of <a href="Paradou%20AC">Paradou AC</a> and <a href="CRB%20Dar%20El%20Be%C3%AFda">CRB Dar El Beïda</a>. The stadium holds 11,000 spectators.
The stadium was used as one of the venues for the <a href="2009%20African%20Under-17%20Championship">2009 African Under-17 Championship</a> and hosted the final of the competition.
